    "title": "Like The Great Rashid Nezhmetdinov!",
    "description": "Download Mproov and Improve Your Chess Today! https://app.mproov.me/AgadYouTube1\n\nSearch all my videos easy https://agadmator-library.github.io/\n\nPhotos by Lennart Ootes\n\nCheparinov, Ivan (2618) - Rapport, Richard (2735) *\nFIDE World Rapid Chess Championship 2023 (Chess.com) [05] 2023.12.26\n\n1.e4 c6 2.Nf3 d5 3.d3 Qc7 4.Nc3 dxe4 5.dxe4 Nd7 6.a4 Ngf6 7.Bc4 Nb6 8.Bb3 Bg4 9.h3 Bxf3 10.Qxf3 e6 11.Bg5 Nbd7 12.O-O Bd6 13.Rad1 h6 14.Be3 g5 15.Rfe1 Rg8 16.Bd4 Rg6 17.Qe2 Be5 18.Nd5 cxd5 19.exd5 Bxd4 20.dxe6 Bxf2+ 21.Qxf2 Nc5 22.exf7+ Kf8 23.Qf5 Kg7 24.Re8 Rxe8 25.Qxf6+\n\nCarlsen, Magnus (2818) - Gareyev, Timur (2588) *\nFIDE World Rapid Chess Championship 2023 (Chess.com) [05] 2023.12.26\n\n1.e4 e5 2.Nf3 Nc6 3.Bb5 a6 4.Ba4 d6 5.O-O Bd7 6.c3 g5 7.d4 g4 8.Ne1 h5 9.Be3 Bh6 10.Qe2 Qf6 11.dxe5 dxe5 12.Nd3 Nge7 13.Nd2 Ng6 14.Nc5 Bc8 15.Rad1 Nf4 16.Bxf4 Bxf4 17.Nd3 O-O 18.g3 Bh6 19.f4 gxf3 e.p. 20.Nxf3 Bg4 21.Qg2 Qe6 22.Bb3 Qe7 23.h3 Be6 24.Nh4 Be3+ 25.Kh2 Qg5 26.Nf5 Bb6 27.h4 Qf6 28.Qe2 Qh8 29.g4 Qh7 30.g5 Kh8 31.Nh6 Bxb3 32.axb3 f6 33.Qxh5 Be3 34.Rde1 fxg5 35.Rxf8+ Rxf8 36.Rxe3\n\nTimestamps:\n00:00 Hello Everyone!\n00:30 Cheparinov vs Rapport\n06:55 Carlsen vs Gareyev\n\nThe FIDE World Rapid Championship is a 13-round Swiss tournament taking place from 26–28 December 2022 in Almaty, Kazakhstan. The prize fund is $350,000, with a $60,000 top prize.\n\nPlayers receive 15 minutes for the entire game, plus a 10-second increment starting from move one. A tie for 1st is decided by two 3+2 blitz games. If still tied, more 3+2 games are played until a player wins. Official website: worldrapidandblitz2022.fide.com\n\nCheck out agadmator's merch here https://teespring.com/stores/agadmators-swag-store\nhttps://teespring.com/design-with-a-story-tm\n\nMailbox where you can send stuff:\n\nAntonio Radić\nAGADMATOR d.o.o.\nFranje Tuđmana 12\nCroatia\n48260 Križevci \np.s. this is not my home address :)\n\nContact me: agadmator@gmail.com \n\nVideo created by OBS\n\n-